‘Accidental definition is composed of genus and one or more properties. Accidents properly so called are expressly rejected as useless in definition by Porphyry, Isag. 8. 15. and by Boethius, Opera, p. 3, though admitted by some subsequent authorities Hence animat risibile would be a better example than Aldrich's animal bipes implume. But the majority of Logicians have very properly regarded accidental definition, in any sorm, as no definition, but merely description. It does not analyse the contents of a action, but enumerates marks by which one individual may be distinguished from each other.
